cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Cross-National GenAI Policy Coding"
message: >-
  If you use this dataset, codebook, or analysis pipeline, please cite the
  accompanying manuscript (currently under double-anonymous review; full
  citation will be added at acceptance).
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: Jie
    family-names: Ni
    email: njie@seu.edu.cn
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0003-9767-5441"
    affiliation: >-
      State Key Laboratory of Digital Medical Engineering, School of
      Biological Science and Medical Engineering, Southeast University,
      Nanjing 211102, China; and Data Science Group, Digital Science
      Centre, University of Innsbruck, Innsbruck 6020, Austria
abstract: >-
  A reproducible open-weight dual-LLM coding pipeline for analysing
  university generative-AI policy text across world regions and languages.
  Includes the 64-institution sampling frame, the 22-query multilingual
  search battery, the eight-theme codebook with sentiment rubric and 16
  worked few-shot examples, 338 dual-LLM coded chunks (Qwen3.6-27B with
  Mistral-Small-3.2-24B cross-validation under schema-constrained JSON
  decoding), 40 expert hand-coded gold-standard chunks, all confirmatory,
  sensitivity, and ablation analysis CSVs, and the full Python analysis
  pipeline.
keywords:
  - generative AI policy
  - cross-national higher education
  - institutional logics
  - large language model coding
  - inter-rater reliability
  - comparative policy analysis
  - reproducible methodology
